Load packages

Map pixel areas to cm^2

PIXEL_CONVERSION_FACTOR = 0.02640625 * 0.01

Load data RAPA

res = read.csv('../data-raw/NF1.ex.csv')
res$Area = (res$Area * PIXEL_CONVERSION_FACTOR)
res$tomerge=paste(res$Pot,res$Tray,sep="_")
stats=data.frame(res)

Load accessions and watering

groups = data.frame(read.csv('../data-raw/TraysAcessions.csv', sep = ";"))
groups$Watering = groups$tray
groups$Tray = groups$tray
groups$tray = NULL

Prepare additional columns

groups$Tray = gsub("D1", "8.W.A.3.a", groups$Tray)
groups$Tray = gsub("W1", "8.W.A.3.b", groups$Tray)
groups$Tray = gsub("D2", "8.W.A.3.c", groups$Tray)
groups$Tray = gsub("W2", "8.W.B.3.a", groups$Tray)
groups$Tray = gsub("D3", "8.W.B.3.b", groups$Tray)
groups$Tray = gsub("W3", "8.W.B.3.c", groups$Tray)
groups$Tray = gsub("D4", "8.W.C.3.a", groups$Tray)
groups$Tray = gsub("W4", "8.W.C.3.b", groups$Tray)
groups$Tray = gsub("D5", "8.W.C.3.c", groups$Tray)
groups$Tray = gsub("W5", "8.W.D.3.a", groups$Tray)
groups$Tray = gsub("D6", "8.W.D.3.b", groups$Tray)
groups$Tray = gsub("W6", "8.W.D.3.c", groups$Tray)

groups$Watering = gsub("1", "", groups$Watering)
groups$Watering = gsub("2", "", groups$Watering)
groups$Watering = gsub("3", "", groups$Watering)
groups$Watering = gsub("4", "", groups$Watering)
groups$Watering = gsub("5", "", groups$Watering)
groups$Watering = gsub("6", "", groups$Watering)

Final merge and adjustment

groups$tomerge=paste(groups$pos,c(groups$Tray),sep="_")

Filter out dates with tray covered

remdates=stats %>%
  filter(!Date %in% c("08-12", "08-16"))

Filter out accessions with less than 2 replicates

mediarapacc = remdates %>%
  filter(!id %in% c("9944", "SALK_045606", "SALK_060946", "SALK_107255", "SALK_137176"))

Calculate means of replicates

mediarapa = mediarapacc %>%
  group_by(id,Watering,Date) %>%
  summarise(meanArea=mean(Area))

Plotting plant size area (mean) by treatment

plotrapa=ggplot(mediarapa, aes(y=meanArea, x=Date, group=id, color=id)) + geom_line() +
  theme_bw() + facet_grid(Watering~ .) + ggtitle ("Plant size area by treatment") +
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 90, hjust = 1))
